s (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://swisscharts.com/charts/jahreshitparade/1991|title=Swiss Year-end Charts 1991|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=November 6, 2015}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|13\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|UK Albums (OCC)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uktop40.republika.pl/najlep%20sprzalbumy%20uk%201991.html |title=Najlepiej sprzedaj\u0105ce si\u0119 albumy w W.Brytanii w 1991r |language=Polish |publisher=Z archiwum...rocka |accessdate=November 6, 2015 |url-status=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927003211/http://uktop40.republika.pl/najlep%20sprzalbumy%20uk%201991.html |archivedate=September 27, 2012 }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|9\n|-\n!Chart (1992)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|European Top 100 Albums<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1992/MM-1992-12-19.pdf|title=European Top 100 Albums, page 17|work=Music & Media|accessdate=November 6, 2015}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|93\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|German Albums (Offizielle Top 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/album-jahr/for-date-1992|title=Top 100 Album-Jahrescharts|language=German|publisher=GfK Entertainment|accessdate=November 6, 2015}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|80\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|UK Albums (OCC)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uktop40.republika.pl/najlep%20sprzalbumy%20uk%201992.html |title=Najlepiej sprzedaj\u0105ce si\u0119 albumy w W.Brytanii w 1992r |language=Polish |publisher=Z archiwum...rocka |accessdate=November 6, 2015 |url-status=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927003211/http://uktop40.republika.pl/najlep%20sprzalbumy%20uk%201992.html |archivedate=September 27, 2012 }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|93\n|}\n\n===Decade-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1990-1999)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Austrian Albums (\u00d63 Austria)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://austriancharts.at/90er_album.asp|title=Best-selling Albums|language=German|work=Austriancharts.at|publisher=Hung Medien}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|34\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications and sales==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Australia|type=album|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|award=Platinum|relyear=1991|certyear=1991|certref=<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mediafire.com/view/?xaij7r71ngxbgqe |title=ARIA Cher data |access-date=2013-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103173028/https://www.mediafire.com/view/?xaij7r71ngxbgqe |archive-date=2013-11-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Austria|type=album|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|award=Platinum|relyear=1991|certyear=1991}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Canada|type=album|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|award=Platinum|relyear=1991|certyear=1991}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|type=album|award=Platinum|relyear=1991|certyear=1996}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|type=album|award=Platinum|relyear=1991|certyear=1992|certref=<ref>[http://www.mediafire.com/view/b1l57842fpfp59p/NZ_chart_book_Cher.pdf Cher in The Complete New Zealand Music Charts]</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Sweden|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|type=album|award=Platinum|certyear=1991|relyear=1991}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Switzerland|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|type=album|award=Platinum|relyear=1991|certyear=1991}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|type=album|award=Platinum|number=3|relyear=1991|certyear=1992|salesamount=1,000,000|salesref=<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1992/MM-1992-07-04.pdf|title=DIANE WARREN WINS UK EMI MUSIC AWARD|publisher=Music & Media, page 4|date=July 4, 1992}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|title=Love Hurts|artist=Cher|type=album|award=Gold|relyear=1991|certyear=1991|salesamount=600,000|salesref=<ref name=\"ussales\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=yes}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cher.com Official website of Cher]\n{{Cher (navbox)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Love Hurts}}\n[[Category:1991 albums]]\n[[Category:Cher albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Guy Roche]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Bob Rock]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Peter Asher]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Richie Zito]]\n[[Category:Geffen Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "Boonzzy", "label": "safe", "comment": "Corrected the incorrect reference to the Billboard 200 chart debuting position - it is not but the peak position.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Love_Hurts_(Cher_album)"}
{"title_page": "Flora Mart\u00ednez", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| image                   = Flora Mart\u00ednez TVyNovelas 2018.png\n| caption                 = Flora in 2018\n| birth_name              = Flora Mart\u00ednez\n| birth_date              = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1977|11|1}}\n| birth_place             = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada\n| death_date              =\n| death_place             =\n| othername               =\n| occupation              = Actress, singer\n| years_active            = 1994-present\n| spouse                  =\n| domesticpartner         =\n}}\n\n'''Flora Martinez''' (born November 1, 1977) is a [[Canada|Canadian]]-[[Colombia]]n film and television actress and singer, best known for her title role in the film ''[[Rosario Tijeras (film)|Rosario Tijeras]]''. Martinez was nominated for [[Goya Award for Best Spanish Language Foreign Film]] in 2005.\n\n== Biography ==\n\nMartinez was born in [[Montreal]] to a Canadian mother and a Colombian father, and raised in [[Bogot\u00e1]] and [[North Vancouver (city)|North Vancouver]].  She began her career in television in Colombia appearing in [[telenovela]]s such as ''Mambo'' (1994), ''[[Mar\u00eda Bonita (TV series)|Mar\u00eda Bonita]]'' (1995), and ''La Otra Mitad del Sol'' (1995). She is a Canadian citizen and speaks fluent French, Spanish and English.\n\nShe studied at the Actors Conservatory in [[New York City]] from 1997 through 1999. In 1999, she appeared in her first feature film, ''Soplo de Vida'', by the Colombian director Luis Ospina, for which she won the Best Actress Award at the [[Biarritz]] Film Festival in [[France]].  She has worked in the theater in the staging of ''Herat'' by Daniel Berardi.\n\nMartinez starred in ''[[Canciones de Amor en Lolita's club|Lolita's Club]]'' (2007), which was directed by noted [[Spain|Spanish]] filmmaker [[Vicente Aranda]].  She is also known in the [[film industry]] for having worked in movies such as ''I'm With Lucy'' (2002), directed by Jon Sherman, and ''Violet of a Thousand Colors'' (2005), directed by Harold Trompetero. She recently starred as the lead of ''[[La Bruja (TV series)|La Bruja]]'' (\"The Witch\").\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#B0C4DE\" align=\"center\"\n! Year || Title || Role || Notes\n|-\n| 1994 || ''Mambo'' || N/A ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1995 || ''Leche'' || Susana ||\n|-\n| ''[[Mar\u00eda Bonita (TV series)|Mar\u00eda Bonita]]'' || Imelda Santos ||\n|-\n| 1996 || ''La otra mitad del sol '' || Isabel ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1999 || ''Divorciada'' || Eva ||\n|-\n| ''Soplo de vida'' || Golondrina/Pilar, the dead woman || Biarritz Film Festival Award for Best Actress<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0555101/awards Awards]. [[IMDb]]. Retrieved December 1, 2011.</ref> \n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Proof of Life]]'' || Linda ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2002 || ''[[I'm with Lucy]]'' || Melissa ||\n|-\n| ''[[The Secret Lives of Dentists]]'' || Female Patient (as Flora Martinez) || \n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Law & Order]]'' || Tina || Episode: \"Seer\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2004 || ''[[La Saga, Negocio de Familia]]'' || Marlene (young) || \n|-\n| ''[[Downtown: A Street Tale]]'' || Maria ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2005 || ''La ley del silencio'' ||Natalia Aguirre ||\n|-\n| ''[[Rosario Tijeras (film)|Rosario Tijeras]]'' || Rosario Tijeras  || [[Cartagena Film Festival]] - Award Golden India for Best Actress<br>[[:es:Festival de M\u00e1laga de Cine Espa\u00f1ol|Malaga Film Festival]] - Award Silver Biznaga for Best Actress\n|-\n| ''Violeta de mil colores'' || Violeta ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2007 || ''Tuya siempre'' || Lola ||\n|-\n| ''[[Canciones de amor en Lolita's Club]]'' || Milena ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2008 ||''Tiempo final'' || Alejandra / Ines ||\n|-\n| ''[[Vecinos (Colombian telenovela)|Vecinos]]'' || Tatiana || Nominat